abstract: ALLENTOWN, Penn., Jan. 12.--The will of Jacob M. Yoder, late of Upper Saucon, Lehigh County, has been probated. The testator leaves his son William, an imbecile, $30,000. The son became insane in 1876, was removed to Kirkbride's, and, after being pronounced incurable, returned to his home. He has a wife and two children. The estate is to be kept in trust for him and after his death is to be divided among the family.

abstract: DETROIT, Jan. 30.--Julius Nagelfeld died at midnight last night under suspicious circumstances.
